---
import Base from '@/layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About" description="About this software engineering blog.">
  <h1>About</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">Who I am and what this is about</p>

  <div class="content">
    <p>
      I'm a software engineer focused on systems thinking, architecture patterns, and applied AI in
      development workflows. This blog explores the intersection of those topics with practical,
      real-world examples.
    </p>

    <h2>What I Write About</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Software architecture and design patterns</li>
      <li>AI-assisted development workflows</li>
      <li>Engineering process and methodology</li>
      <li>Practical deep dives with code examples</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Tech Stack</h2>
    <p>
      This blog is built with Astro, React islands for interactivity, TypeScript, and Zustand for
      state management. Content is managed through Astro content collections with MDX.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .subtitle {
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    margin-bottom: 32px;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .content {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .content h2 {
    margin-top: 28px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .content p {
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .content ul {
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    padding-left: 24px;
  }

  .content li {
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
</style>
